[
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Web Application Security Testing Guide:  n for Information Gathering and Session Analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "1. Introduction",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "This document provides a comprehensive collection of curl commands for web application security testing, focusing on information gathering, application architecture mapping, website mirroring, cryptography testing, business logic testing, and session management testing. Each command includes a detailed explanation of its purpose, execution details, expected output, and security implications.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2. URL Structure Analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Understanding the URL structure of a target application is fundamental to effective security testing. The following commands help analyze and map URL patterns.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.1 Extracting and Categorizing URLs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.1.1 Extract All Links from the Homepage",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://example.com | grep -o 'href=\"[^\"]*\"' | sed 's/href=\"//g' | sed 's/\"//g' | sort | uniq > urls.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image22.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Harvests all hyperlinks from the target website's homepage for further analysis.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-s: Silent mode, suppresses progress meter and error messages",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -o 'href=\"[^\"]*\"': Extracts all href attributes from HTML tags",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sed 's/href=\"//g': Removes the \"href=\" prefix",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sed 's/\"//g': Removes remaining quotation marks",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sort | uniq: Sorts alphabetically and removes duplicates",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "> urls.txt: Saves results to a file for further analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image13.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A text file containing all unique URLs found on the homepage.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Helps identify potentially sensitive areas of the application, API endpoints, and resource patterns that might not be immediately apparent.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.1.2 Categorize URLs by Pattern",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep \"/product/\" urls.txt > product_urls.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep \"/category/\" urls.txt > category_urls.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep \"/api/\" urls.txt > api_urls.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep \"login\\|signin\\|auth\" urls.txt > auth_urls.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image21.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image12.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Organizes discovered URLs into functional categories for targeted testing.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "These commands filter the previously extracted URLs based on common patterns",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Each pattern is saved to a dedicated file for further analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Multiple text files, each containing URLs that match specific functional categories.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Helps identify application structure and critical endpoints for more focused security testing.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.2 Advanced URL Discovery",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.2.1 Extract URL Parameters from JavaScript",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://example.com/main.js | grep -o \"url.*?\" | grep -o \"?[^'\\\"]*\" > parameters.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image23.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Identifies URL parameters that might be used in AJAX requests or other dynamic content loading.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Downloads JavaScript file(s) from the target application",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Uses regex to extract URL patterns and parameters",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Saves parameters to a dedicated file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A list of URL parameters used in JavaScript, potentially revealing undocumented API endpoints.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Exposes parameters that might be vulnerable to injection attacks or capable of controlling sensitive functionality.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2.2.2 Discover Hidden API Endpoints",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://www.w3schools.com | grep -o '<script[^>]*src=\"[^\"]*\"' | grep -o 'src=\"[^\"]*\"' | cut -d'\"' -f2 | while read script; do",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "if [[ ! $script =~ ^http ]]; then",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "if [[ $script =~ ^// ]]; then",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "script=\"https:$script\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "else",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "script=\"https://www.w3schools.com$script\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "fi",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "fi",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s \"$script\" | grep -oE '/api/[^\"]+' | sort -u",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "done",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image11.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Examines all loaded JavaScript files to identify references to API endpoints that may not be visible in the HTML content.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Extracts all script source references from the target page",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Properly handles relative and absolute URLs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Downloads each script and searches for API endpoint references",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Consolidates and de-duplicates findings",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A list of API endpoints referenced in JavaScript files.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Reveals potentially sensitive API endpoints that might not be properly secured against unauthorized access.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3. Session Management Analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Understanding how applications manage sessions is critical for security testing. These commands help identify and analyze session mechanisms.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.1 Identifying Session Storage Mechanisms",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.1.1 Examine Cookies Set During Initial Visit",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -v https://example.com 2>&1 | grep -i \"set-cookie\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image19.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image32.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Identifies cookies set by the application during the initial visit, which often include session identifiers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-v: Enables verbose output to see headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2>&1: Redirects stderr to stdout since curl outputs headers to stderr",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -i \"set-cookie\": Filters for cookie-setting headers, case-insensitive",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A list of Set-Cookie headers returned by the server.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Reveals how the application initiates session tracking and what information is stored in cookies.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.1.2 Save and Examine Cookies",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Save cookies to a file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -I -c cookies.txt https://example.com",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Display cookie contents",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "cat cookies.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image28.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Captures all cookies set by the application and allows detailed examination of their attributes.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-c cookies.txt: Saves cookies to the specified file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "The file format includes domain, path, secure flag, expiration, name, and value",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A structured file containing all cookie details.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Allows assessment of cookie security attributes such as HttpOnly, Secure flags, expiration times, and domain scope.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.2 Extracting Session Identifiers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.2.1 Extract Session Cookie Values",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -i \"sessionid\\|phpsessid\\|jsessionid\" cookies.txt | awk '{print $NF}'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image20.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Isolates session identifier values from cookies for use in further testing.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -i: Searches case-insensitively for common session cookie names",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "awk '{print $NF}': Prints the last field, which is the cookie value",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Raw session identifier values without additional cookie attributes.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Allows analysis of session ID entropy, predictability, and structure, which can reveal weaknesses in session management.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.2.2 Capture Post-Authentication Session",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -c auth_cookies.txt -X POST https://example.com/login \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-d \"username=test&password=test123\" \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image16.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image33.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image14.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image17.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Simulates a login attempt and captures the resulting authenticated session cookies.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-X POST: Specifies POST method for form submission",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-d: Provides form data for authentication",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "The field names (username, password) must be adjusted based on the actual form",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: A cookie file containing authentication and session cookies set after login.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Enables comparison between pre-authentication and post-authentication cookies to identify session establishment patterns.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3.2.3 Extract and Store Session ID for Testing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "SESSION_ID=$(grep -i \"sessionid\" auth_cookies.txt | awk '{print $NF}')",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Use it in a subsequent request",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -b \"SESSIONID=$SESSION_ID\" https://example.com/protected-area",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image2.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Extracts a session identifier for use in subsequent requests to test session management.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "First command extracts and stores the session ID in a variable",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Second command uses the session ID to access a protected resource",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-b: Sets the specified cookie in the request",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: The response from the protected resource if the session is valid.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Establishes a foundation for session manipulation tests and session management bypass attempts.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4. Information Gathering - Review Web Metadata",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "These commands help identify potentially sensitive information exposed through HTTP headers and HTML metadata.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.1 Basic HTTP Header Analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.1.1 Collect Server Information Headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -E 'Server|X-|Content-|Date'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image1.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Retrieves HTTP headers that may reveal information about the server technology stack.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-I: Sends a HEAD request to retrieve only headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -E: Filters for specific header types that commonly leak information",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: HTTP headers that might reveal server software, version, frameworks, and custom headers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Excessive information disclosure in headers can help attackers identify vulnerabilities specific to the revealed technologies.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.1.2 Check for Security Headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -E 'X-XSS-Protection|X-Frame-Options|Content-Security-Policy|Strict-Transport-Security'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image31.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Identifies the presence or absence of security-related HTTP headers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Filters specifically for security headers that protect against common web vulnerabilities",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Any security headers implemented by the application.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Missing security headers may indicate vulnerability to attacks like XSS, clickjacking, or transport layer security issues.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.2 HTML Metadata Analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.2.1 Extract HTML Meta Tags",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://example.com | grep -o '<meta[^>]*>'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image8.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Gathers meta tags from HTML which may contain sensitive information.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -o: Outputs only the matching part of the line",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Pattern matches complete meta tags",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: All meta tags from the page HTML.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Meta tags might reveal CMS information, author details, or internal documentation references that could be useful for attackers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.2.2 Extract HTML Comments",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://example.com | grep -o '<!--.*?-->'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image15.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Extracts developer comments from HTML that may contain sensitive information.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Pattern matches HTML comment syntax",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: All HTML comments in the page source.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Comments often contain debugging information, credentials, or other sensitive data inadvertently left by developers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.3 Application Information Resources",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4.3.1 Retrieve robots.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s https://example.com/robots.txt",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image27.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Examines the robots.txt file which may reveal directories the site owner wishes to keep private.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Simple direct request to the robots.txt file at the domain root",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
