    "text": "These commands help identify the underlying technologies and architecture of the target application.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "5.1 Server Technology Identification",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "5.1.1 Identify Web Server and Technology Stack",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -i 'server\\|x-powered-by'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image29.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Determines the web server software and potential framework information.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-I: Sends a HEAD request to retrieve only headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "grep -i: Case-insensitive search for server technology indicators",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Headers that reveal server software (Apache, Nginx, etc.) and frameworks (PHP, ASP.NET, etc.).",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Knowing the exact technologies allows for targeted exploitation of known vulnerabilities.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "5.1.2 Detect Web Application Firewall (WAF)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I -X GET \"https://example.com/?test=<script>alert(1)</script>\" | grep -i 'server\\|x-powered-by\\|waf'",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image26.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Tests for the presence of a WAF by sending a basic XSS probe.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Sends a request with a simple XSS payload",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Looks for WAF indicators in the response headers",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Headers may reveal WAF presence or custom security headers if a WAF is active.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: WAF detection helps determine the level of protection and whether more sophisticated bypass techniques are needed.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "5.2 Framework and Backend Detection",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "5.2.1 Check for Cookie Technology Indicators",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -i 'set-cookie'",
