    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6. Session Management Testing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "These commands help evaluate the security of the application's session management implementation.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.1 Session Fixation Testing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.1.1 Test for Session Fixation Vulnerability",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Step 1: Capture an unauthenticated session",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -c unauth_cookies.txt http://testphp.vulnweb.com",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image5.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Step 2: Extract the session ID",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "UNAUTH_SESSION=$(awk '/sessionid/ {print $NF}' unauth_cookies.txt | tail -n 1)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Step 3: Attempt login while maintaining the same session ID",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -b unauth_cookies.txt -c post_login_cookies.txt -X POST http://testphp.vulnweb.com/login.php \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-d \"test%2Ftest\" \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image18.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Step 4: Extract the new session ID after login",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "NEW_SESSION=$(awk '/sessionid/ {print $NF}' post_login_cookies.txt | tail -n 1)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Step 5: Compare session IDs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "if [ \"$UNAUTH_SESSION\" = \"$NEW_SESSION\" ]; then",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "echo \"VULNERABLE: Session ID not regenerated after login\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "else",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "echo \"SECURE: Session ID regenerated after login\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "fi",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image4.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image37.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Tests whether the application regenerates session IDs upon login, which is essential to prevent session fixation attacks.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "First obtains an unauthenticated session",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Attempts login while maintaining the same session ID",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Compares pre-login and post-login session IDs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Indication of whether the session ID changes after authentication.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: If session IDs are not regenerated after authentication, the application is vulnerable to session fixation attacks.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.2 Session Expiration Testing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.2.1 Test for Session Timeout",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Login and capture session",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -c auth_cookies.txt -X POST https://example.com/login \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-d \"username=test&password=test123\" \\",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Extract session ID",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "SESSION_ID=$(grep -i \"sessionid\" auth_cookies.txt | awk '{print $NF}')",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Test access to protected resource immediately",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -b \"SESSIONID=$SESSION_ID\" https://example.com/profile -o /dev/null -w \"Initial Access: %{http_code}\\n\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Wait for potential timeout period (e.g., 30 minutes)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "echo \"Waiting for 30 minutes to test session timeout...\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sleep 1800",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "# Test access again after waiting",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -b \"SESSIONID=$SESSION_ID\" https://example.com/profile -o /dev/null -w \"After Timeout: %{http_code}\\n\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Evaluates whether the application implements proper session timeout mechanisms.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Authenticates and captures a valid session",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Tests immediate access to a protected resource",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Waits for a reasonable timeout period",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Tests access again to see if the session has expired",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: HTTP status codes indicating whether access is still granted after the timeout period.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Lack of proper session timeout increases the risk of session hijacking, especially on shared computers.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.3 Cookie Security Attribute Testing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.3.1 Check for Secure and HttpOnly Flags",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -i \"set-cookie\" | grep -i \"secure\\|httponly\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image9.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Verifies if cookies are protected with the Secure and HttpOnly flags.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Examines Set-Cookie headers for security attributes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Secure flag ensures cookies are only sent over HTTPS",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "HttpOnly flag prevents JavaScript access to cookies",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Expected Output: Cookie headers showing whether these security flags are present.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Security Implications: Missing Secure flag allows cookie transmission over unencrypted connections; missing HttpOnly flag increases XSS risk.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "6.3.2 Test for SameSite Attribute",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "curl -s -I https://example.com | grep -i \"set-cookie\" | grep -i \"samesite\"",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image24.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose: Determines if cookies have SameSite attribute to prevent CSRF attacks.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Execution Details:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Examines Set-Cookie headers for the SameSite attribute",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "SameSite can be Strict, Lax, or None",
